text: Am I the only one who didn't like the first Deadpool movie that much? I know it was a big milestone getting an R rated superhero movie, but that isn't really a necessity when you have a character who can reference the censors. The bar was set low on accuracy to so I guess most people didn't notice or didn't care about the mistakes to his character. Like him being a mutate, not a mutant. They totally ditched that connection to Wolverine. They also removed a lot of his moral ambiguity. Brutally killing your opponents can make you an antihero, but Deadpool is a straight up mercenary and is a flat-out villain sometimes. (I know he was a villain in X-Men Origins: Wolverine, but we don't talk about that movie) They made his wounds taking too slowly, having him regrow his hand to baby size in hours, as opposed to the minutes it should've taken to grow to regular size. Then while his teleportation belt and magic satchel are not necessary to include, they are some of the most entertaining parts of the character and it's a same we couldn't see them. That's why I'm personally glad a studio that has respect for the source material is getting control of Deadpool.

Now getting a trailer is hype though, don't get me wrong, but i would've liked it a bit more if we were given just a tiny bit more information on why we should care for this kid, even something very vague would suffice for me. Now it feels like watching a trailer for Independence day without having the general knowledge about the series (and therefore not knowing that it's always about an alien invasion) and just seeing a bunch of people being scared about something without being shown or even remotely hinted at what this threat is (Russians? Do you think of how they were to have that place, in everything they are connected. Notice the episode in "The Gifted" when they talked about how they first got their hiding place, and please remember this aired a year or so before "Deadpool 2" ( https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R90vRuZOOnY ). After you watch tell me what does that sound like to you? They know what they're doing. text: Deadpool 2 is bigger and funnier than the first movie I love this movie. I will say it is not as good as the first movie by like 1 percent but it is funny as hell. I loved all the references and jokes in this movie. Ryan Reynolds is awesome as Deadpool and Josh Brolin is awesome as Cable and Zazie Beetz who plays Domino is just great and I loved Karan Soni who reprises his role as Dopinder the cab driver he was hilarious. And Julian Dennison who plays Firefist/Russell is great And of course the rest of the cast was excellent there is some celebrity cameos especially the X-Force characters. And I am happy that they actually used characters from the comics. Spoiler there is a X-Men character in this movie that is done way better than in X-Men 3 The Last Stand and that character is Juggernaut he is so much better in this movie and I was really happy with him they redeemed themselves by making the right Juggernaut that you see in the comics and on the TV show. The acting, story, action, comedy, directing and special effects are great. I really loved this movie hope they do another one. If you have not seen this movie then I recommend you do. This movie is cinematastic rating 5/5
